    "UIName": "Arion",
    "Id": "chassisdef_Arion_1",
    "Name": "Arion",
    "Details": "The Arion, developed by Clan Hell's Horses, is a versatile hybrid combat unit designed for both BattleMech and tank configurations. Equipped with an ER Large Laser and two SRM-4 launchers, the Arion is capable of delivering devastating firepower at medium to long ranges. With a top speed of 97 km/h, it can rapidly traverse the battlefield and reposition as needed. The Arion's conversion capability allows it to operate as either a fast, heavily armed BattleMech or a heavily armored tank with a low profile, depending on the mission's needs. In BattleMech mode, the Arion is capable of agile and dynamic movements, thanks to its quadrupedal design. When converted to a tank, the Arion provides an armored, low-profile platform with a powerful punch. Despite its versatility, the Arion is not as heavily armored as traditional BattleMechs, and its conversion process takes time and resources, making it less effective in rapidly changing combat situations. Nevertheless, its ability to perform in multiple roles makes it a valuable asset in a wide range of missions.\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Quirk: QuadVee Mech</color></b>\n\n<b><color=#e62e00>Drop Cost Multiplier: 1.06</color></b>",
